 John Shiklam in Kaduna One of the All Progressives Congress (APC) governorship aspirants in Kaduna State, Sani Sha’aban, has rejected the outcome of the primary election, describing the process as a sham. He alleged that there were no delegate congresses anywhere in the state, maintaining that the process was manipulated. Senator Uba Sani, was on Friday morning, declared winner of the primary election, polling 1,149 votes. Sha’aban and another aspirant, Bashir Abubakar scored 10 and 37 votes respectively. However, addressing a press conference in Kaduna, Sha’aban said the election as a charade as due process was not adhered to.